# Cline Rules for cv-builder
# Auto-loaded by Cline at the start of every task.

## MANDATORY: Read project instructions first

At the start of every task, read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` in full.
It is the authoritative reference for this project and contains:
- Critical data-safety rules (NEVER lose user data)
- Architecture overview, runtime boundaries, and config schema
- Critical workflows (commands, test runners, session lifecycle)
- Project-specific patterns and gotchas
- Available slash commands and /obo session management

## Available Skills

User-level shared skills live in `/Users/warnes/src/vscode-config/.github/skills/`.
Repo-local skills live in `codex-skills/`.

Key skills to apply proactively:

| Skill directory | When to apply |
|---|---|
| `copilot-preflight/` | Before every multi-step or code-change response |
| `copilot-instructions-bridge/` | When needing cross-project context |
| `implementation-planning/` | When planning a new feature or refactor |
| `sequential-code-review/` | During code review tasks |
| `one-by-one/` | For sequential item processing with `/obo` |
| `cv-builder-patterns/` | cv-builder-specific code patterns |
| `cv-ui-review/` | Evaluating the web UI |
| `unit-testing/` | When generating or fixing tests |
| `git-workflow/` | For commit, branch, and PR operations |
| `commit-message-generator/` | When generating commit messages |
| `markdown-formatting/` | When writing/editing Markdown documents |
| `python-patterns/` | Python code style and idioms |

To read a skill: `read_file` on `SKILL.md` inside the relevant directory.

## Available Slash Command Prompts

Prompt files live in `/Users/warnes/src/vscode-config/prompts/` (also symlinked to
`~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/prompts/`). Reference these by name when
the user invokes them:

- `/preflight` → `preflight.prompt.md`
- `/plan` → `plan.prompt.md`
- `/obo` → `OneByOne.prompt.md`
- `/codeReview` → `codeReview.prompt.md`
- `/cvUiReview` → `cvUiReview.prompt.md`
- `/commitMessage` → `commitMessage.prompt.md`
- `/unitTest` → `unitTest.prompt.md`

When the user invokes a slash command, read the corresponding `.prompt.md` file and
follow its instructions.

## /obo session management

Helper: `/Users/warnes/src/vscode-config/.github/skills/one-by-one/obo_helper.py`
Session dir: `.github/obo_sessions/`

Always check for existing sessions before starting a new one:
```bash
python /Users/warnes/src/vscode-config/.github/skills/one-by-one/obo_helper.py sessions --base-dir /Users/warnes/src/cv-builder
```

## MCP Tools available in Cline

- **obo-mcp**: `obo_create`, `obo_list_items`, `obo_mark_complete`, `obo_update_field`
  Use these for /obo sequential-processing sessions.
- **markitdown**: Convert documents/URLs to Markdown for reading.